The **Tidy** Preferences panel lets you select the default Tidy configuration
options. Options set in this panel will be applied to new documents, or to
documents that you open. Documents that are already open are not affected.

These settings are also the settings that will be used when using one of the
[System Services][service] or [Action Extensions][extension].

<% if target_feature?(:feature_supports_applescript) %>
These are also the settings that <%= pne %> will use when using
AppleScript to Tidy files.
<% end %>


![tidy prefs panel](all-tidy-prefs-Tidy){: .dropshadow}

The Preferences window can be re-sized when looking at this panel, which should
provide plenty of space for working with the Tidy options.


